Author: sassygillie
Text: I do this too. One time I grilled 6 medium-sized shrimp (without any oils or butter, just plain) and went to enter it in to MFP. Well, shrimp is incredibly low calorie, like 80cals for those 6 pieces. I checked a whole bunch of entries and googled for other sources and they all said the same thing. My disordered ass was convinced that it tasted too good to be that low so I added 3tbsp of butter “just in case some old food rubbed off the grill”

Author: BladderPatrol
Text: I don’t trust food that tastes good.
